org.mxupdate.test
Class ExportParser.Line

java.lang.Object
  org.mxupdate.test.ExportParser.Line
Enclosing class:
ExportParser
public final class ExportParser.Line
extends Object

The class is used to build a hierarchy of lines depending of the shifting where the text of a line begins. The shifting for all children of a line is always greater.

Example:

 mql mod form "${NAME}" \
     description "DESCRIPTION" \
     field name "ABC1" \
          add setting "ABC1" "DEF" \
     field name "ABC2" \
          add setting "ABC2" "DEF"
This source code builds a structure of lines like (tag names with the value in braces):
  • mql (mod form "${NAME}")
    • description ("DESCRIPTION")
    • field (name "ABC1")
      • add (setting "ABC1" "DEF")
    • field (name "ABC2")
      • add (setting "ABC2" "DEF")
